overview:
Grant is the co-founder and CEO of Tred, a seed-funded online car buying startup. Tred allows new car shoppers to test drive from their doorsteps and buy from their iPads. Grant was encouraged to make Tred his full-time focus when an angel offered to write him a check as soon as he quit his day job in 2011. Since then, Grant has incubated Tred at General Assembly in New York and at TechStars in Seattle, where the company is currently based.

Prior to Tred, Grant worked in private equity and automotives at Pacific Coast Capital Partners (formerly Lehman Brothers), Lowe Enterprises and BMW. He was raised in Seattle and studied at the University of Southern California and Harvard Business School.
